cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about language style transfer, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CL (Computation and Language) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also proposes a multi-agent system that uses techniques like denoising auto-encoder and back-translation, which are commonly used in machine learning and deep learning. This suggests that the paper could also be categorized under cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of neural models, which are often used in tasks related to neural networks and deep learning, such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses the Bible as a dataset, which could suggest that it falls under the sub-category of computer vision (cs.CV) if the text is treated as an image.
